 {"id":"bd-2n73.17","title":"Unit tests: manifest parser + registry normalization","description":"Build comprehensive unit tests for ACFS manifest v2 parsing and tool registry normalization. Cover schema validation, dependency expansion, tag/phase filtering, install/verify command extraction, and error messaging. Include golden fixtures for representative module sets and edge cases. Success: manifest parsing is stable and well specified independent of runtime tool detection.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:26:41.375010310Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:14.349423867Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.17","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:26:41.375010310Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.17","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:07.194529259Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.17","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:14.349333507Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"bd-2n73.18","title":"E2E: tool inventory + setup readiness (with detailed logging)","description":"Create Playwright E2E scripts that validate tool inventory and setup readiness against a real gateway instance: manifest-driven tool list, detection status, auth badges, and install/verify summaries. Capture console/network/WS logs, screenshots, and traces using the E2E logging framework. Success: setup/readiness UI is verified end-to-end with rich diagnostics.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:26:52.817686794Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:38.506385124Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.18","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:38.506298351Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.18","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:33.123414322Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.18","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:26:52.817686794Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.18","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:26.303873466Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.18","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:21.533363110Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"bd-2n73.19","title":"E2E: utilities workflows (giil/csctf/xf/toon) with logs","description":"Add Playwright E2E scripts for utilities workflows: giil image fetch, csctf transcript export, xf archive search, and toon output viewer. Use the E2E logging framework to capture stdout/stderr mapping, API responses, and UI rendering. Success: utilities are fully validated end-to-end with detailed diagnostics and reproducible artifacts.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:00.816827320Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:54.533844453Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.19","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:54.533756697Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.19","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:49.506284924Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.19","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:00.816827320Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.19","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T19:27:44.774145425Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"bd-2n73.2","title":"ACFS manifest ingestion + tool registry sync","description":"Implement a manifest ingestion layer in gateway that reads ACFS manifest v2 (acfs.manifest.yaml) and normalizes modules into tool registry entries (id, category, phase, tags, install/verify commands, robot/MCP metadata hooks). Include schema validation, caching, and a public endpoint to expose parsed modules. Add golden fixtures for valid/invalid manifest cases and ensure parsing errors are reported cleanly. Success: gateway can drive tool inventory/health from manifest instead of hard-coded lists.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:37:21.531341678Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T19:26:02.195466682Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.2","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:37:21.531341678Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.2","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:39:21.111680219Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
